## Quiz Discussion

- Suppose you are given a data frame containing 150 observations of 5 variables describing the physical attributes of 3 groups (e.g. species) of flowers. Describe one way to visually differentiate between sample groups in the data?
- How would you use the grammar of graphics (Wilkinson 2005) and ggplot2 (Wickham 2009) to create this visualization?Â  You may use ggplot syntax or close psuedo-code to describe the graphic(s) you have in mind.


## Quiz Discussion

- Define or provide three examples of "chartjunk" according to Tufte (2001).
- Chartjunk refers to all visual elements in charts and graphs that are not necessary to comprehend the information represented o the graph, or that distract the viewer from this information.

- http://www.sealthreinhold.com/tuftes-rules/rule_three.php

## Quiz Discussion

- Define the Golden Rectangle? How does it apply to graphics according to Tufte (2001)?


